reviews.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on April 16, 2020
reviews.name: Daniel F.
reviews.title: Easily overclocked and durable
reviews.review: I've been running this continually overclocked to match the specs of an 8350 (at 4.0 GHz) for 4 years now and it's never had a single problem. Though it's starting to show it's age and I'm nearing time for an upgrade, it's worth saying thank you AMD for making something that held up.

reviews.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on March 13, 2020
reviews.name: Mason Qualls
reviews.title: Bent pins and uneven thermal paste.
reviews.review: I was so excited to get the package because my old one is sloow. I took it out, took off the heat sink, then out with the old in with the new. After getting it in first try (go me!) I powered it up then no video. Light and everything else spinning except no video. I reset the ram and tried everything. I looked at the pins after taking it out and realized 2 were bent. I will be sending this back soon when I get the time and getting a refund if I can.
